	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			Here is what you need to know to do this quest for the Bull Hammer.  Red V spawns 24 hours an EQ day.  The spot is in the South East corner of the mines of malfunction.  He is level 5 to 7.  He drops an imcomplete blackbox which you fill blackbox fragments.  Not scrap metal.  Hit combine, and turn the result in to Manik Compelton.  You have a random chance no matter what your faction to get the Bull Hammer.  6 damage, 20 delay, 2 str, 2 agi, 2 dex weapon.  Dwarf, gnome, and halfling.  Cleric, paladin, shadowknight, ranger, warrior, and shaman.  1H blunt.  Non magic.  I know people to have gotten it on their first or second try, and others on their 25th.  I got it on my 24th.  The people I know that got it on the first and second time had indifferent faction with Manik.  I had warmly by the time I was finished.  This weapon is great for any level, because it is the best 1H blunt in the game as far as damage delay ratios.  Only problem is that it won't hit magic.  When you turn in the rusted blackbox to Manik, you may also get rusty weapons, small patchwork armor, small wooden shield, small raw-hide, or Iony's Absorber.  The absorber is a worthless held item that gives 5 poison and disease resistance.  When you try to kill Red V, root him when he runs, or sit down.  Don't chase him because he often runs out of the mines to the guard, and gets slaughtered, leaving no corpse.  The worst part about waiting for the spawn is that the evil caster guild masters cast constantly.  The sound is annoying, and the spam is atrocious.  Don't EVER attack the skels.  They are level one, but are invincible to attack, and spells.  Worse yet is that the guild masters nearby will kill you FAST.  Another note.  You can get blackbox fragments from runaway clockworks outside in Steamfont.  So go collect them while Red V is being camped by someone else.  Oh, and a little side note, Red V comes from Star Wars.  That was Luke Skywalker's designation when they were going to destroy the Death Star.  And then there is that other quote in Highpass from the princess behind the fake wall, &quot;Aren't you a little short for a Highpass Guard?&quot;  That comes from when Luke rescued Leia in the Death Star, and she said &quot;Aren't you a little short for a Storm Trooper?&quot;  Just thought you might like to know.
			</font>
	
		</td>
	</tr>
	
