	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			It is not the quest for the brutechopper ( a 2H slashing weapon).  It is the quest for the Bullsmasher and if you are a small (DWF GNM HFL) character, it is worth every minute you spend there to get the item.  It is one of the best items in the game when you consider that you can use another weapon to hit magical creatures (the Bullsmasher is not magical.)  Faction has very little to do with this quest.  If Manik Compolten gives you the quest, you can get the Bullsmasher.  On Karana, it has sold for 200-400pp but if you get it DO NOT SELL IT.  With 6dam and only 20del, it is better than Bladed Thulian Claws.  To top it off, it adds +2 STR, AGI, DEX.  I know a couple of warriors that began training in the art of one handed blunts just to be able t ouse this weapon.  As for the faction, a dwarf cleric friend of mine with no faction adjustments got it on the first try, but a gnome warrior friend gave up after the 21st try.  I myself have failed at the quest 7 times, but I will remain in the mines until the bullsmasher is mine!
			</font>
	
		</td>
